'''Pirojpur Sadar''' ({{lang-bn|<U+09AA><U+09BF><U+09B0><U+09CB><U+099C><U+09AA><U+09C1><U+09B0> <U+09B8><U+09A6><U+09B0>}}) is an [[Upazila]] of [[Pirojpur District]] in the Division of [[Barisal Division|Barisal]], [[Bangladesh]].

==Geography==
Pirojpur Sadar is located at {{coor d|22.5778|N|89.9900|E|}}  . It has 41893 units of house hold and total area 278.37 km<U+00B2>.

==Demographics==
[[As of 1991]] Bangladesh [[census]]{{GR|Bangladeh}}, Pirojpur Sadar has a population of 225156. Males constitute are 50.93% of the population, and females 49.07%. This Upazila's eighteen up population is 116628. Pirojpur Sadar has an average literacy rate of 50.7% (7+ years), and the national average of 32.4% literate. <ref name="census">{{cite web |  accessdate = November 10 | accessyear = 2006 |  url = http://www.bangladeshgov.org/mop/ndb/arpc91_v1/tables04.htm | title = Population Census Wing, BBS.}}</ref>

==Administrative==   
Pirojpur Sadar has 13 Unions/Wards, 130 Mauzas/Mahallas, and 143 vilages. 


